{{wikipedia|Abessive case}}
==English==
===Noun===
'''caritive case'''

#{{grammar}}: [[case]] used to express the [[lack]] or [[absence]] of something. It has the meaning of the English preposition "without." The caritive case is found in some [[Caucasian]] languages.

